Vegetarian Ramen with Shiitake and Soft Eggs
  --Cook's Country

3 tbsp toasted sesame oil
8 oz shiitake mushrooms, stemmed and sliced
6 scallions, cut into 1" pieces
2" piece ginger, peeled and cut into matchsticks
2 tbsp white miso
8 c vegetable broth
3x3 oz package ramen noodles, seasoning packet discarded
2 oz (2 c) baby spinach
4 soft cooked large eggs*, halved
chili garlic sauce

Heat oil in large dutch oven over medium high heat until just smoking. Add mushrooms and scallions and cook until lightly browned and tender, ~ 5 min. Stir in ginger and miso and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Whisk in broth and bring to boil. Add ramen and cook, stirring occasionally to break up noodles, until tender, ~3 min. Off heat, stir in spinach. Divide into 4 bowls, top each with 1 egg. Serve with chili garlic sauce.


*For soft eggs with set whites and fluid yolks, boil for 6 min
